Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.66,0:00:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This graph shows the Beijing PM2.5 index during January 2013
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.86,0:00:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In just one month, there were 25 days of smog
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.58,0:00:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in Beijing at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.06,0:00:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and as I looked back on this curve over the course of that year,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.46,0:00:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to recall the senses and emotions
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.58,0:00:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.86,0:00:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time everyone said
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.50,0:00:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the haze was caused by
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.70,0:00:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,random weather patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hardly anyone took it seriously
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.18,0:00:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In that month, I made four business trips:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.14,0:00:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaanxi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.18,0:00:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Henan
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.94,0:00:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Jiangxi
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.90,0:00:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Zhejiang
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.22,0:00:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking back at the sky of these trips,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.26,0:00:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems like China at that time was immersed in smog
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.18,0:00:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,blanketing 25 provinces
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.30,0:00:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and 600 million people
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.58,0:00:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was right in the middle of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.94,0:00:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn't even realize it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.42,0:00:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But the sensation in my throat remained
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.26,0:00:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was in Xi'an, I was coughing so badly that I couldn't even sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.58,0:00:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I cut up a lemon and put it beside my pillow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.26,0:00:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When I returned to Beijing,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.62,0:00:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I discovered that I was pregnant
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.54,0:00:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what she looked like the first time I saw her
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.38,0:00:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, I knew she must be a girl
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.10,0:00:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it looked like she had a girl's haircut
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.06,0:01:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard her heartbeat for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.66,0:01:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing I wanted more than for her
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.66,0:01:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to be healthy
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.30,0:01:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.06,0:01:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,she was diagnosed with a benign tumor
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.74,0:01:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,which would require surgery immediately after birth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.78,0:01:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the anaesthesia,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.50,0:01:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor told me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.86,0:01:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your baby is so young that there is a possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.46,0:01:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,she won't survive the general anaesthetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.42,0:01:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be mentally prepared for it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.94,0:01:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I could even hold her,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.94,0:01:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,she was carried off to the operating room
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.02,0:01:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, the nurse gave me a toy bear
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.38,0:01:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,which she used to comfort children
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.74,0:01:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, she used it to comfort me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.06,0:01:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw my little angel after the surgery,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.14,0:01:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,she was still unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.66,0:01:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor said,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.50,0:01:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“The operation was very successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.14,0:01:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is one thing you have to forgive me for:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.46,0:01:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,She is so chubby that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.34,0:01:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it took several attempts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.42,0:01:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a vein for the anesthetic.”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.06,0:01:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I took her tiny hand, full of needle marks,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.50,0:01:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and I held it to my face
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.94,0:02:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I called her name
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.10,0:02:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,until she opened her eyes and looked at me
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.62,0:02:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a very lucky person
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.42,0:02:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I quit my job so I could
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.06,0:02:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,spend my time keeping her company and looking after her
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.26,0:02:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as we are all together, safe and sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.06,0:02:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing else matters
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.42,0:02:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.58,0:02:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,already on our way home from the hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.34,0:02:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I started to feel scared
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.94,0:02:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The smell of black smoke and burning fire was everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.46,0:02:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I covered her nose with my handkerchief
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.46,0:02:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how stupid that seems,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.34,0:02:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,since in her struggle to breathe through it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.18,0:02:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,she would just breathe in more smog
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.86,0:02:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that moment, I'd never been afraid of air pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.62,0:02:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd never worn a filter mask
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.98,0:02:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, there is a little life in your arms
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.30,0:02:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,her breathing, eating and drinking are all on your shoulders
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.14,0:02:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when you begin to feel afraid
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.86,0:02:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That severe smog at the end of 2013 lasted about two months
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The continuing smog made me feel like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.14,0:02:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it was more than just a random occurrence
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.06,0:02:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and that it couldn't possibly be over quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.54,0:02:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the same sky that I saw ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.26,0:02:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was in Shaanxi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.54,0:03:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: “Is it like this every day?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.10,0:03:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy: “Every day of every year, it's like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.02,0:03:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's lasted for three years now,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.42,0:03:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,not just a day or two.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.54,0:03:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Benzopyrene is a powerful carcinogen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.00,0:03:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As time goes on, it accumulates in one's body
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Once enough of it accumulates,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.70,0:03:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it increases a person's risk of getting cancer.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.34,0:03:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: “Sir, do you think this is still a river?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.98,0:03:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wang: “It's not river water, it's wastewater.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.46,0:03:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Tests show that the annual average
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.46,0:03:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,benzopyrene level here is 290 times above the regulatory limit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.54,0:03:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Person: “All of the trees over there died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.22,0:03:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Those two big trees there have completely split open.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.30,0:03:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: “Have you ever seen a real star before?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.70,0:03:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Wang Huiqing: “No, I haven't.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.02,0:03:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: “What about blue sky?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.22,0:03:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wang Huiqing: “I've seen one that's a little blue.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:03:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: “What about white clouds?”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.70,0:03:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wang Huiqing: “No, I haven't.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When I interviewed this six-year-old girl in 2004,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.98,0:04:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it didn't cross my mind at all that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.66,0:04:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what she said
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.14,0:04:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,could be the same experience my daughter would have
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These photos show each day of 2014 in Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.34,0:04:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Only when the air quality was good
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.62,0:04:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,would I dare take my daughter outside with me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.38,0:04:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But how many good days were there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,175 were polluted
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.54,0:04:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That means that in one year, half of the time I had no choice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.06,0:04:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but to keep her at home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.98,0:04:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,like a prisoner
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten years ago, the director of the Environmental Protection Bureau told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.30,0:04:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“Xiaoyi is a microcosm of Shaanxi;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.14,0:04:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaanxi is a microcosm of China.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.14,0:04:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In just a decade,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.62,0:04:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I've looked on helplessly as this has come true
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.94,0:05:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I once watched a TV series
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.06,0:05:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,titled "Under the Dome"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.98,0:05:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about a small town
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.06,0:05:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly enclosed by a dome that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.34,0:05:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared out of nowhere
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut off from the world, no way out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.42,0:05:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But one day, I realized that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.26,0:05:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we're all living in the same reality
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.74,0:05:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, when I get up in the morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.06,0:05:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I see my daughter standing in front of our balcony smacking the glass window
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is her method of telling me that she wants to go outside
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, one day, she will ask me
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.90,0:05:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mama, why do you keep me shut inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.30,0:05:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What is really out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.26,0:05:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Will anything hurt me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.10,0:05:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I have done
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.90,0:05:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout this year
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.26,0:05:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is to answer the questions
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.26,0:05:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,she will ask me in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What is smog?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.22,0:05:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does it come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.94,0:05:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:05:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is the smog?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.62,0:06:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, I turn off the light
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.98,0:06:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.18,0:06:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that PM2.5 is here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.30,0:06:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're airborne particles
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.70,0:06:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,with a diameter of 2.5 micrometers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.42,0:06:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So they reflect a large amount of visible light,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving us in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.42,0:06:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,with very low visibility
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.86,0:06:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I can't see them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because the smallest particle the naked eye can see
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.82,0:06:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,... is twenty times bigger
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.82,0:06:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.30,0:06:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a war against an invisible enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.42,0:06:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.82,0:06:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to see them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.34,0:06:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.18,0:06:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a PM2.5 sampling device
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.22,0:06:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I put a very clean sampling filter
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,into the machine
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.06,0:06:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and carried it for 24 hours
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.10,0:06:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what the filter looked like at the very beginning, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.50,0:06:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,After 24 hours
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it looked like this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.02,0:06:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't do anything to protect my child
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.42,0:06:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,she will breathe in all of this stuff
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.74,0:06:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How much will she breathe in?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,305.91 micrograms per cubic meter
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.62,0:07:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But who can understand a number like this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only compare it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.94,0:07:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the WHO standard for maximum PM2.5 per day
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.98,0:07:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the standard in the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.62,0:07:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the standard in Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.18,0:07:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the standard in China
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.94,0:07:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How much
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.22,0:07:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,did we breathe in on that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.10,0:07:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost 5 times China's maximum limit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.02,0:07:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it sounds like
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.98,0:07:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that was just one slightly alarming number
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.90,0:07:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to know what substances were
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.58,0:07:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,actually in that sample
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Prof. Qiu Xinhua from Peking University was kind enough to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.74,0:07:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,run this test for me
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.70,0:07:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are the results of his analysis:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.10,0:07:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It contains 15 types of carcinogens
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.98,0:07:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,including
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.46,0:07:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,benzo[a]pyrene
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.62,0:07:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the world's strongest carcinogens
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.74,0:07:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times the standard was there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.50,0:07:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,14 times the government standard
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't believe this number
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.22,0:07:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in that clip,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.46,0:07:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was standing in Xiaoyi,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.62,0:07:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,surrounded by coal plants?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The amount of Benzo[a]pyrene I was breathing there was only 9 times the legal standard
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.42,0:07:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowadays, I live in the center of an international metropolis
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.46,0:07:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When I look around, I can't see a single factory or chimney
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.30,0:07:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So how can it possibly be 14 times the legal limit?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.14,0:07:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Qiu doubted the results too
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.62,0:07:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He said “It doesn't seem possible to be that high.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.86,0:08:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll run it again.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.90,0:08:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He called me the next day and told me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.30,0:08:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“There was no mistake; it is 14 times the limit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.10,0:08:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Our wider sampling showed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.30,0:08:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,there are some people whose exposure was even higher than yours
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.38,0:08:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,-- 20 times the legal limit.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All these carcinogens were stuck to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.98,0:08:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the sampling filter
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.14,0:08:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you saw before
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.86,0:08:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to a substance called black carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.94,0:08:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's tiny,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.82,0:08:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,only 0.2 micrometers
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.42,0:08:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But it has a chain structure,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.82,0:08:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,so if it is unraveled
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,two grams is the size of ...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.34,0:08:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a basketball court
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.66,0:08:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this, it can absorb many carcinogens and heavy metal particles\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.30,0:08:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How much black carbon is there in China?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.62,0:08:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is NASA's estimate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.86,0:08:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from 2009
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.74,0:08:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That bright purple and white spot
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.10,0:08:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is China
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It drifts above us like a ghost
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.42,0:08:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went to Peking University
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.14,0:08:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that they have a lab for these experiments
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.94,0:08:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked an expert if I could volunteer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.54,0:08:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“If you put me in a closed chamber with a high concentration of black carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.98,0:08:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and observe and test my physical reactions,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I can show everyone the results.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.98,0:09:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He hesitated for a while and answered
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.42,0:09:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot do this experiment.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.30,0:09:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.74,0:09:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “Every experiment ...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.30,0:09:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,requires academic ethical thresholds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.58,0:09:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The thresholds should prevent extreme harm
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.54,0:09:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to the participants.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.82,0:09:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot run an experiment with these thresholds
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.54,0:09:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if the concentration in the air outdoors
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.54,0:09:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is higher than in the test chamber."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.66,0:09:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“To put it another way,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,each of us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.34,0:09:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is living in an experimental chamber our entire life
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.98,0:09:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and we don't know what the outcome of the experiment will be.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.90,0:09:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Peking University used a different approach
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.46,0:09:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They logged how people physically
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.58,0:09:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,react to polluted air directly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.70,0:09:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,For one year,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.10,0:09:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I participated in this experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what I found:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.54,0:09:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I have chronic respiratory inflammation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.82,0:09:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and belong to a sensitive population group
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.46,0:09:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine particles impact the respiratory system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,exacerbate inflammation of the respiratory tract
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.30,0:09:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and affect the entire cardiovascular system
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.06,0:09:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Tiny particles correlate with a higher possibility of heart failure due to reduced cardiac blood supply
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.18,0:09:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really understand
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.50,0:09:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,what the medical jargon means
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore with the help of the scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.22,0:09:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we made an animation to explain the effect
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.06,0:10:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I am PM2.5
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.06,0:10:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have lots of brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.10,0:10:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons and other heavy metal particles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.42,0:10:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of bearing weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.98,0:10:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In the game of attacking human bodies
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I rarely miss
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.14,0:10:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Scene 1
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.38,0:10:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nostril
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.42,0:10:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nose hairs and mucus can block large particles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.54,0:10:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,90% of particles are bigger than 10 microns
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.98,0:10:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and get killed in action
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.82,0:10:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But they cannot stop me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.62,0:10:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Scene 2
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.54,0:10:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Throat
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.58,0:10:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The upper respiratory tract
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.30,0:10:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,has cilia that are only 10 microns long
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They beat 20 times
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.54,0:10:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.50,0:10:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but I pass through them with ease
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The smooth muscles of the trachea become irritated,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.90,0:10:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,contract and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.46,0:10:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,try to block me,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.70,0:10:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but this bullying can't stop me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.50,0:10:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Scene 3
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.34,0:10:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower respiratory tract
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.70,0:10:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Here the bronchi branch out like a tree
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.34,0:10:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,into small bronchioles
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.70,0:10:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the best ski slopes for us
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.30,0:10:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We fight with leukocytes and lymphocytes along the way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.50,0:10:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,These fights will cause all kinds of inflammation in the human body
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.26,0:11:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Our troop finally reaches our destination:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the tree-tip like alveoli
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.30,0:11:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The human lung has more than 300 million alveoli
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.90,0:11:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If we block the alveoli,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.70,0:11:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the human won't be able to breathe anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.78,0:11:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,However, our most ferocious enemy is here: the macrophages
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.78,0:11:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Their specialty is gobbling up foreign material
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.10,0:11:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and are known as the body's street sweepers
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.46,0:11:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be a tough battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.18,0:11:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However we outnumber them
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.02,0:11:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,our core is difficult to break down,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and and we contain toxic heavy metals
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Macrophages cannot neutralize all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and can be easily killed by over-consumption
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.90,0:11:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how the human immune system breaks down
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.58,0:11:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We have another special force:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.98,0:11:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,particles less than 0.5 microns
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.94,0:11:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in the alveoli, they are small enough to pass the membranes into blood vessels
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.74,0:11:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,damaging the blood vessel lining
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.94,0:12:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and causing arteries to narrow
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.18,0:12:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which causes high blood pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and thrombosis
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.58,0:12:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We can even enter the core of human bodies through the pulmonary circulation system
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.86,0:12:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and attack your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.78,0:12:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,causing myocardial ischemia and irregular heartbeat
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.06,0:12:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which leads to heart attacks
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.78,0:12:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Be terrified,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.14,0:12:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,humans
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.26,0:12:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in every breath
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.62,0:12:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you take
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.14,0:12:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,These measurements
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.90,0:12:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,were provided by the Chinese Academy of Sciences
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.18,0:12:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This complex plot demonstrates
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.70,0:12:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that as the concentration of PM2.5 increases,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.30,0:12:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the human mortality rate also increases
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Many other scientific research institutions have observed the same trend
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.58,0:12:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Chen Zhu, the former Chinese health minister
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.02,0:12:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,has calculated that
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.02,0:12:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the number of premature deaths
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.86,0:12:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,caused by air pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.26,0:12:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in China each year is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.26,0:12:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,500,000 people
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.74,0:12:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In this battle against human beings,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.46,0:12:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the most fragile and vulnerable populations are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.90,0:13:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,our children and parents
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.66,0:13:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,These babies are about 2 months old
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.86,0:13:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They have never been outside
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but they have been diagnosed with pneumonia
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.46,0:13:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they are receiving nebulizer therapy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.34,0:13:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The parents of these babies asked me to photograph their children
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.54,0:13:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,they suspected their children became sick
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.78,0:13:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,due to lack of protection during heavy smog
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.66,0:13:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The doctor told them:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.22,0:13:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“I can only render a diagnosis of 'Pneumonia of unknown cause'
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.58,0:13:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the lack of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.46,0:13:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,current epidemiological studies.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.34,0:13:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can tell you this statistic:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.22,0:13:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In January of 2013
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.66,0:13:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,during the heavy smog,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the entire country,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.42,0:13:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,27 cities
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.38,0:13:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,showed exponential increases in emergency department visits.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.66,0:13:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The mothers in my community
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.34,0:13:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,discussed about this event once
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.02,0:13:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One mother asked me:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.06,0:13:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“How should we deal with the smog?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.54,0:13:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we expose our kids
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to the smog
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.06,0:13:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as soon as possible to train them, so they adapt
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.62,0:13:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and aren't disadvantaged from the very beginning?”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.38,0:13:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A medical expert from Los Angeles,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.62,0:13:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,a city that once suffered from extreme air pollution, informed us
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.62,0:13:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,about the risks of exposing our children
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.94,0:13:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to air pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.06,0:14:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in hopes that they would be able to adapt to the conditions:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.38,0:14:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think we have any information
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.62,0:14:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that suggests that exposing your child to air pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is going to help them to adapt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.18,0:14:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If we expose them on day one,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.54,0:14:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they lose some function.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.38,0:14:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If they expose them on day two,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.66,0:14:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't lose the same amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.58,0:14:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's because, not that they have adapted,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.18,0:14:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but because they've already lost the function,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.18,0:14:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and they already are injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.46,0:14:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It has been shown in several studies around the world now,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.62,0:14:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that children in cleaner places grow faster
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.50,0:14:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,than children growing up in a more polluted area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.94,0:14:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor lung function early in life
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.82,0:14:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is a predictor of lung problems later on in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.54,0:14:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.38,0:14:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,doing something about the air while a child is growing
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.82,0:14:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make a change in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.30,0:14:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that child's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.42,0:14:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is downstairs from where I live
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.66,0:14:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and I took this photo two days ago in severe smog
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.02,0:14:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The AQI (air quality index) on that day
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.06,0:14:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,had exceeded 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,above the “hazardous” pollution level
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.70,0:14:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the kids in the adjacent elementary school
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.78,0:14:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,were still outside playing ball games, running and playing around
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.14,0:14:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When people exercise
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.26,0:14:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,they breathe five to ten times more deeply than usual
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.90,0:14:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw this,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.78,0:15:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I became aware of the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.42,0:15:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't protect my child under all circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.42,0:15:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Someday she will have to go into society
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.50,0:15:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and breathing is something she will always do,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.78,0:15:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,something that is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.46,0:15:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And it (PM2.5) is there in every breath you take
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.46,0:15:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,An adult person like ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.78,0:15:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,breathes roughly 25000 times each day
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.42,0:15:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Over time, as it accumulates continuously,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.46,0:15:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,what are these substances like
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.58,0:15:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,in our lungs?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.70,0:15:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We are very grateful to a patient and doctor
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.54,0:15:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,at Beijing Cancer Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.26,0:15:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who agreed to let us film this surgery
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.50,0:15:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a patient with early stage lung cancer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.18,0:15:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Female, in her fifties
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.74,0:15:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and works in the hospital's accounting office
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.50,0:15:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She and her family have no history of smoking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.58,0:15:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone will breathe in these black spots
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.74,0:15:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Including ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.86,0:15:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this person smoke?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.70,0:15:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, she doesn't smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.78,0:15:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But she's from (censored) city
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.38,0:15:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,From your hometown
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.54,0:16:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The air quality is really bad
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.62,0:16:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's not clean (there)\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.38,0:16:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So this (might be) the stuff that's in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.06,0:16:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In her entire body only the lymph nodes in her lungs are black
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.62,0:16:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is because she has inhaled a lot of dust
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.78,0:16:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The lymphatic system is crucial for immune system functionality
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means it helps our immune system fight disease
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.94,0:16:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When the black stuff on top accumulates
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.42,0:16:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,does it affect our body's ability to fight cancerous cells?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.02,0:16:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It may be the case that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.06,0:16:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it has overburdened the lymphatic system
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.02,0:16:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So this year the World Health Organization (WHO)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.66,0:16:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,has reported that chronic lung diseases
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.54,0:16:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,are one of the highest risk factors for lung cancer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We can be comforted by the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.58,0:16:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,this type of surgery is very successful
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.70,0:16:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and the patient can make a full recovery
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.70,0:16:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,after the tumors have been extracted
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.14,0:16:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,After extracting the black lymph nodes,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.26,0:16:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor presented them to the patient's family
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.42,0:16:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They asked:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“Can you tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.74,0:16:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,why my wife got cancer?”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.86,0:16:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, “I can only say that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.70,0:16:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,according to my clinical experience
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.86,0:16:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I suspect it was because of air pollution.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.34,0:17:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,WTO told me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.70,0:17:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“particle matter is classified as
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.54,0:17:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a primary carcinogen for humans.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.70,0:17:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When he told me this I had a question:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't lung cancer
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.46,0:17:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,have an incubation period
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.74,0:17:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,of at least ten years or so?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.86,0:17:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But we only started hearing about air pollution two years ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how could it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.34,0:17:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,lead to lung cancer this quickly?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.86,0:17:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went to NASA
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.58,0:17:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for a small favor
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.34,0:17:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and asked if they could send over satellite images
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of the air over North China from the past 10 years
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.58,0:17:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what I got
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.06,0:17:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,2012
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The air over Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.66,0:17:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,2011
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.10,0:17:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Beijing in December
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.90,0:17:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,2010
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.34,0:17:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The air over North China
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.62,0:17:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,2009
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.18,0:17:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The air over North China
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.22,0:17:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at 10 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.10,0:17:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,North China in 2005
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.86,0:17:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't believe it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was living under these skies in North China at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.78,0:17:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I have been unaware of any air pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.22,0:17:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for 10 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So I sought out our country's
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.74,0:17:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,head of the Olympic air quality assurance group
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.42,0:17:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,An academic named Dr. Tang Xiaoyan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.06,0:17:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She gave me this graph
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.98,0:17:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 2004
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.78,0:17:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Eleven years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.34,0:17:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, we hadn't yet started monitoring PM2.5 levels
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.98,0:18:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have the levels of PM10
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.26,0:18:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,She said according to estimates at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.14,0:18:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.58,0:18:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,when it was very polluted
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.70,0:18:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,PM2.5 could have reached 300-400
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.38,0:18:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Today we would classify that as very unhealthy pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.26,0:18:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked her
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.18,0:18:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it really be that I was that blind?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.26,0:18:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in Beijing in 2004
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.14,0:18:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, look at this picture
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.22,0:18:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.42,0:18:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, that's probably smog, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.42,0:18:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how come I didn't know at the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.02,0:18:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, you should look up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.98,0:18:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,what the news headlines were on that day
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.90,0:18:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“Beijing Capital Airport Experiences 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the Most Delays in Recent Years Due to Fog”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.90,0:18:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then we thought it was just fog
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.70,0:18:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We kept calling it “fog”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.10,0:18:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So after I saw this picture,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as a former reporter
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.34,0:18:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was full of remorse
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because all those years I was reporting I always thought that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.38,0:18:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I was reporting on pollution across the country
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.26,0:18:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But I always thought
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.38,0:18:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it was only called pollution when I heard explosions in mines
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.18,0:18:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it was only called pollution when I saw smoke from factory chimneys
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.34,0:18:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.38,0:18:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that those of us who lived in a metropolitan urban center
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.10,0:18:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the sky we saw everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.58,0:18:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,was also pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.54,0:18:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time I wasn't a reporter anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.14,0:18:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had already become a bystander
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.62,0:19:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But I still had a question
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.26,0:19:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If it really was like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.10,0:19:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was young every family
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.38,0:19:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,was burning kerosene stoves, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.30,0:19:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Every night we would
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.10,0:19:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,sleep and awaken to the smell of smoke\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.38,0:19:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How come I never heard
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,about people back then getting lung cancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.10,0:19:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept asking this question
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.42,0:19:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,until I met professor He Xingzhou
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.62,0:19:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,who has been researching this topic for over 30 years
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.38,0:19:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave me a book of data
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.14,0:19:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.54,0:19:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A Survey of the Relationship {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}between Air Pollution and Cause of Death for 26 Chinese cities{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.46,0:19:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}1976-1981{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.14,0:19:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone can see clearly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.42,0:19:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I've put the conclusion up on the screen here
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.70,0:19:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very simple
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.86,0:19:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The air pollution from back then
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.54,0:19:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,already correlated with death rates from lung cancer
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.46,0:19:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The air pollution back then
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.50,0:19:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was the result of burning coal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.14,0:19:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It just happened to be the case that this data
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.98,0:19:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was considered internal information at that time
