Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.06,0:39:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That took a hundred years in other countries
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.26,0:39:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, on top of the pollution from coal
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.34,0:39:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to count in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.98,0:39:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The pollution from oil as well
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.06,0:39:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So what happens to our oil?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.10,0:39:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of our oil is burnt by vehicles
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.86,0:39:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In ten years, the number of China’s vehicles
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.22,0:39:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Has increased by about 100 million
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.54,0:39:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How many more cars do we have solely in Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.90,0:39:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Through year 2010?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.06,0:39:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,800,000 more
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.02,0:39:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What do 800,000 cars mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.06,0:39:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If we connect all these cars
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.94,0:39:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Head to tail
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.30,0:39:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They can line up from Beijing to Shenzhen
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.58,0:39:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And then back to Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.66,0:39:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the amount of increase
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.18,0:39:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In just one year
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.94,0:39:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The primary PM2.5 source local in Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.34,0:39:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the vehicles
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.26,0:39:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is another city that surprised me
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.94,0:39:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This city is under haze for
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.46,0:39:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,over 200 days per year
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.34,0:39:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You may guess which city that is
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.02,0:39:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.62,0:39:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s try another picture
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.54,0:39:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Qinghai you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.10,0:39:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Qingdao?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.78,0:39:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That is Hangzhou
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.18,0:40:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To be honest I am as shocked as you are
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.66,0:40:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I always thought
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.38,0:40:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the scenes in misty rains as described in those famous poems
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.82,0:40:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Later I made a call
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.02,0:40:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To the Ministry of Environmental Protection in Hangzhou
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.78,0:40:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They confirmed this
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.90,0:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the number of vehicle ownership per capita in Hangzhou
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.42,0:40:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the largest among all cities in China
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.10,0:40:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,On average, every two people own a car
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.22,0:40:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the vehicles of Hangzhou
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.38,0:40:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Contribute nearly 40% of its air pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.38,0:40:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Do more cars necessarily mean more pollution?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.50,0:40:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s a question we often hear
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.74,0:40:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren’t there more cars in Tokyo than in Beijing?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.42,0:40:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t we see
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.26,0:40:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Such severe pollution in Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.46,0:40:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the explanation given by the Beijing Municipal Commision of Transport:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.26,0:40:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,More than 90% of residents in Tokyo
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.50,0:40:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Are riding on rail transportation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.94,0:40:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Only less than 6% of them drive in cars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.26,0:40:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What about in Beijing?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.90,0:40:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,34% of Beijing residents drive cars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.70,0:40:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And they drive in the central area of the city
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.86,0:40:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually stuck in traffic jams
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.26,0:40:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When they are stuck their cars are idling
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.46,0:40:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The emission become twice as much
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.62,0:40:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they brake, more heavy metals are released
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.98,0:40:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So every day during the peak hours in Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.34,0:40:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How much PM2.5 is emitted in one hour
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.94,0:40:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the 6th ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.58,0:40:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A ton.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.18,0:40:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How many Beijing residents would choose to drive
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.86,0:40:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,When they are going somewhere within 5km?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.74,0:40:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Close to a half
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.18,0:41:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,12% of all residents
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.82,0:41:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Would drive within 2km
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.94,0:41:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And 7%
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.46,0:41:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Would drive within 1km
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.66,0:41:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How far is 1km?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.74,0:41:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s only the distance you travel when heading to a supermarket
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.14,0:41:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a green grocery
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.98,0:41:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we really love driving so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.38,0:41:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps a few of us do
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.06,0:41:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But there can’t be so many irrational people, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.42,0:41:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My family owns a car
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.94,0:41:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But after our child was born we made a rule
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.58,0:41:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically we would only drive for our parents, our kid
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.26,0:41:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Or when we go to the airport or hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.38,0:41:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When my husband goes to work every day
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.86,0:41:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He rides a bicycle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.82,0:41:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is how you ride a bicycle
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.26,0:41:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In front of our apartment building
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.90,0:41:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the only way to ride
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.26,0:41:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.22,0:41:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our bicycle lane
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.02,0:41:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s almost always under some cars
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.70,0:41:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There are over 5 million vehicles in Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.82,0:41:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Only half of them have a parking space
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.98,0:41:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But no car can park in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.46,0:41:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So you find them on bicycle lanes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.06,0:41:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And pedestrian lanes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.54,0:41:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And pedestrian lanes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.14,0:41:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, humanity is the same throughout the world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.22,0:41:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Without regulations, this can happen anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.82,0:41:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s check London
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.58,0:41:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems they also parked like this in the old days
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.54,0:41:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the parking meters were installed
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.54,0:42:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And they parked like this
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.22,0:42:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then London raised its
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.38,0:42:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,parking fee and congestion charge
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.26,0:42:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So they parked like this
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.74,0:42:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A few days ago, I heard that people are trying the same thing in Shenzhen
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.38,0:42:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They started to charge high parking fees
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.90,0:42:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the fellowmen in Shenzhen parked like this
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.98,0:42:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Same things happened in Tokyo 50 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.66,0:42:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not that easy
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.58,0:42:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It took them a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.86,0:42:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To clear the cars out of the way one by one
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.74,0:42:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This pose a test
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.22,0:42:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To the detailed city management
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.66,0:42:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Car-lovers have another question
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.86,0:42:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,As this photo shows
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.82,0:42:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There are no vehicles in Beijing at midnight, are there?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.86,0:42:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is the pollution still so severe?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.26,0:42:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really caused by cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.86,0:42:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This question also troubled me for long
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.26,0:42:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Until the Chinese Academy of Sciences showed me this chart
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.70,0:42:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Before every dawn in Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.98,0:42:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s always a peak of pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.66,0:42:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows up everyday constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.50,0:42:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And its organic carbon emission is always about twice higher
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.10,0:42:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Than the peak in the afternoon of the same day
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.38,0:42:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What on earth is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.50,0:42:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know the answer as well
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.74,0:42:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So we went to Yanqing (a subdivision county of Beijing)
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.18,0:43:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector: halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.54,0:43:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector: This truck doesn’t have the basic equipments for National Standard 4 (it’s labeled as standard 4)
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.46,0:43:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: so in fact it’s not a standard 4 vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.14,0:43:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Driver: then what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.06,0:43:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Driver: I just bought this new truck
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.70,0:43:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Driver: this is my environmental protection label
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.14,0:43:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: it’s issued this year
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.62,0:43:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: what does 3.29 mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.02,0:43:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector: it’s above the limit
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.18,0:43:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector: this is even below the National Standard 1
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.42,0:43:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: so it has no emission control device at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.42,0:43:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector: no, basically no emission control at all
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.14,0:43:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector: he has the green label
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.38,0:43:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It says National Standard 3
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.62,0:43:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: who issued it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.26,0:43:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Department of Environmental Protection of Hebei Province
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.98,0:43:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Driver: when I bought it they said it was Standard 3
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.42,0:43:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I know? I was just buying a truck
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.66,0:43:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector: His truck is on the green channel
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.94,0:43:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It carries eggs, milk and oil
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.50,0:43:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s part of the city’s supply system
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.86,0:43:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,According to regulations
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.70,0:43:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We should not penalize this car
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.58,0:43:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Li: Fake cars are common
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.06,0:43:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Or if we put it in more serious terms, fake cars are everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.70,0:43:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a secret kept within automotive industry
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.06,0:43:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,90% of basic environmental protection devices are not installed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.94,0:43:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: Then what would the emission become?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.46,0:44:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Li: If 30,000 vehicles enter the city
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.34,0:44:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It equals to several million vehicles running on the road at night
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.74,0:44:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Without any emission devices
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.14,0:44:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How would the emission be?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.38,0:44:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The amount of particulate emission alone
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.98,0:44:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of just one vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.82,0:44:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is 500 times the emission from a vehicle of
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.10,0:44:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,National Standard 4
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.98,0:44:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The diesel cars do not take a big proportion among vehicles
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.66,0:44:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s similar to the case of scattered coal
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.90,0:44:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not many
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.82,0:44:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 17% of all cars
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.14,0:44:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But their emission of nitrogen oxides
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.22,0:44:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Takes 70% of all automotives’ emission\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.70,0:44:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What about their emission of primary particles
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.42,0:44:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Related to all automotives?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.54,0:44:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s 99%
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.50,0:44:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The more dreadful fact is
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.02,0:44:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The particulates in diesel vehicle emission
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.46,0:44:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Have exceptionally high toxicity
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.78,0:44:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The PAHs (Polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons) are carcinogens
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.06,0:44:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.14,0:44:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Diesel vehicles release the upgraded version of PAHs
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.66,0:44:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The nitro-PAH
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.78,0:44:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Its carcinogenicity is one magnitude higher
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.86,0:44:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw those drivers
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.74,0:44:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Of diesel vehicles in Yanqing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.94,0:44:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized they themselves are the victims
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.38,0:44:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Most deeply harmed by the diesel emission
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.82,0:44:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the high-risk group to have cancers
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.46,0:44:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, it is most unreasonable to punish these people
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.86,0:45:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They spent their own money
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.06,0:45:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They bought the vehicles with legal certificates
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.66,0:45:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Issued by the government
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.82,0:45:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What reason do we have to fine them?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.46,0:45:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If we want to blame someone
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.86,0:45:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn’t we start from those
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.18,0:45:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are responsible for fake vehicle manufacturing?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.58,0:45:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know how our African brothers would feel after hearing this
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.90,0:45:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A business always has its arguments
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.34,0:45:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Or reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.46,0:45:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But what makes me curious is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.42,0:45:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,For more than ten years
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.42,0:45:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If such fake manufactories exist widely
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.90,0:45:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And commonly
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.78,0:45:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And are known to the supervision departments
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.10,0:45:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren’t they dealt with?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.54,0:46:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t we have the law?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.02,0:46:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t we have the regulations
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.14,0:46:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To recall defective automotive products?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.38,0:46:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Such products can surely be recalled, aren’t they?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.30,0:46:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,However, from year 2004 to this day
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.26,0:46:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times have this law been used
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.62,0:46:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On this kind of vehicles?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.74,0:46:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even once
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.86,0:46:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.78,0:46:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the answer I got
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.58,0:46:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Only when the defects pose unreasonable danger
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.98,0:46:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Towards the safety of people or their properties
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.74,0:46:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the product be recalled
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.02,0:46:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They say
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.06,0:46:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving environmental protection devices out of manufacturing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.10,0:46:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Has nothing to do with safety
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.02,0:46:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It won’t kill anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.54,0:46:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So there’s no reason for recalling
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.10,0:46:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do we have the right to fine the manufactories
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.18,0:46:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Or let them destroy their products?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.66,0:46:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We do
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.50,0:46:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Law of Prevention and Treatment of Atmosphere{\i0} states that
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.34,0:46:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can make these factories stop their illegal production
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.10,0:46:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You can fine them
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.62,0:46:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also confiscate and destroy their products
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.10,0:46:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Since year 2002
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.02,0:46:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,More than ten years have passed
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.94,0:46:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times has this law been used?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.58,0:46:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even once
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.30,0:46:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.18,0:46:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the answer I got
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.70,0:46:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This law can only be enforced
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.34,0:46:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By the departments
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.58,0:46:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That have the legal supervision right
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.50,0:46:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone says
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.74,0:46:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know which department that is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.66,0:46:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Since there are only a few departments
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.50,0:47:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Related to automotive management
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.14,0:47:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I just called them one by one
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.54,0:47:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,First I asked the Ministry of Environmental Protection
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.22,0:47:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They say
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.62,0:47:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as we know, it’s not us
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.34,0:47:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I asked the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.06,0:47:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They say: It’s absolutely not us
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.26,0:47:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I asked the General Administration of Quality Supervision and Inspection
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.82,0:47:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They say
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.90,0:47:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That should be all three of us
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.54,0:47:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they do have the reason to be confused
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.38,0:47:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why doesn’t the law
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.62,0:47:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just clarify who is in charge of this management?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.06,0:47:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to turn to the NPC (National People’s Congress)
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.82,0:47:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So I called the NPC
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.54,0:47:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is their reply:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.50,0:47:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The executive subject of this law is indeed unclear
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.34,0:47:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very rare case
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.42,0:47:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In our legislation process
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.54,0:47:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would it exist nowhere else
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.14,0:47:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the Article 53 in the Law of Atmosphere?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.78,0:47:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ding : We asked them (NPC) back then
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.82,0:47:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you write the Law of Atmosphere like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.34,0:47:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you just let us take charge of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.42,0:47:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They replied that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.94,0:47:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when they were making this law
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.82,0:47:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Many departments opposed it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.26,0:47:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying that the MEP (Ministry of Environmental Protection) should not be in charge
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.30,0:47:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the bill could not pass
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.14,0:47:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end they (NPC) had to use
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.94,0:47:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,A vague term to make it pass
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.14,0:47:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So it says that only the departments with executive right can enforce this law
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.22,0:47:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: so it sounds like the three departments are all responsible for supervision\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.26,0:47:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ding: but in reality we cannot control it
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.78,0:47:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Their certificates are all valid
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.82,0:48:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So are the vehicles’ types
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.14,0:48:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The MEP also issued them green labels
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.78,0:48:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Of National Standard 4
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.70,0:48:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single department would check the cars’ emission standard
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.74,0:48:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is in fact only on National Standard 1
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.34,0:48:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: if you claim to have the executive right
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.42,0:48:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No one can deny that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.62,0:48:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you just execute the law?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.54,0:48:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ding: the MEP is surely not doing their best
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.22,0:48:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I admit this
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.82,0:48:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.86,0:48:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn’t go further
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.02,0:48:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chai: then after so many years
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.26,0:48:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you have any power for law enforcement?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.90,0:48:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ding: we can’t really try to enforce the law nowadays
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.54,0:48:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise they will see how powerless we actually are
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.94,0:48:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the awkward thing about MEP
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.38,0:48:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Embarrassed is not only Environmental Protection Agency(EPA)
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.78,0:48:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Car companies should also be embarrassed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.14,0:48:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The fraud car business owner told me later
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.38,0:48:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If EPA can enforce the law,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.82,0:48:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to catch those fraud cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.30,0:48:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I will make sure we build the real car next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.70,0:48:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.22,0:48:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We build real one,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.82,0:48:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Others build fraud one,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.78,0:48:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We will be bankrupt tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.22,0:48:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I ask Ding Yan,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.10,0:48:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think this is reasonable?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.06,0:48:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He said Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.14,0:48:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Not enforcing the law is making other people forge.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.90,0:48:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Car companies had another way to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.54,0:48:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Say we are National IV standard
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.90,0:48:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,has already made sure it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.94,0:48:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let everybody get new cars
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.86,0:48:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But National IV gasoline are still missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.34,0:48:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the gasoline quality is not good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.90,0:49:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When we are in Yan Qing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.58,0:49:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Randomly checked this diesel truck
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.06,0:49:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This diesel got from Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.70,0:49:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It is already very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.82,0:49:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Highest level in China
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.46,0:49:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the test result come out,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.46,0:49:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Its (sulfur content) is 25 times higher
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.18,0:49:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,than European, Japan and US
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.10,0:49:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the type of diesel quality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.62,0:49:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How about our gasoline?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.38,0:49:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a table I got from Chinese Research Academy of Environmental Science(CRAES).
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.50,0:49:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I saw this table, I feel painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.58,0:49:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I cannot understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.54,0:49:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing is they gave me a conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.26,0:49:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This means our national fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.22,0:49:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,normally two or three level lower than developed country.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.86,0:49:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one level higher,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.30,0:49:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We can reduce 10% of emission.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.14,0:49:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like we have some good fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.86,0:49:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We have National IV and higher fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.38,0:49:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But these are only 3% of total.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.98,0:49:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the pain of Hangzhou
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.82,0:49:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hangzhou has money
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.18,0:49:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to buy good fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.38,0:49:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is nothing before 2013
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.58,0:49:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,After struggle some time,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.98,0:49:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you can only burn National III fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.22,0:49:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.30,0:49:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like our sulfur content
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.46,0:49:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is really close to European country
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.58,0:49:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Close to US
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.06,0:49:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you look at the four items below
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.22,0:49:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Some data that we cannot understand at all
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.02,0:50:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some danger behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.26,0:50:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Either they are
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.98,0:50:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,increasing oxidative in atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.06,0:50:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Become small particle
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.98,0:50:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Or increasing poisonousness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.46,0:50:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one is increasing pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.10,0:50:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It increased
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.70,0:50:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the pressure of gasoline evaporation to the air
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.78,0:50:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I origionaly thought it can only evaporate a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.54,0:50:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then CRAES pro told me
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.34,0:50:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this clip
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.62,0:50:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is filmed by infrared ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.62,0:50:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if gas station don’t add
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.66,0:50:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,this fuel gas recycle part,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.26,0:50:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It can evaporate a lot like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.46,0:50:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,1.5 gram per 1 liter (0.2 oz per US gallon)\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.22,0:50:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Into atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.46,0:50:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And our normal car’s tank
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.14,0:50:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,will evaporate by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.10,0:50:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,How strong is its evaporate power?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.58,0:50:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In Beijing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.98,0:50:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,hydrocarbon comes from evaporated
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.06,0:50:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is higher than exhaust
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.02,0:50:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the main part of PM2.5
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.46,0:50:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why don’t we make the fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.82,0:50:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,cleaner?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.94,0:50:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The petrochemical industry told us this.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.62,0:50:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,National Standard is not high enough
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.26,0:50:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This sentence seems reasonable
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.22,0:50:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You don’t have reason to require company produce
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.26,0:51:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,higher standard fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.58,0:51:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.22,0:51:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I asked
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.50,0:51:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,EPA, CRAES
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.14,0:51:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Those people who involved in making the standard
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.06,0:51:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you make the standard higher?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.18,0:51:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the answer he gave me
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.30,0:51:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This small standard committee (Oil fuel and lubricant technology committee)
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.94,0:51:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the people in this industry
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.10,0:51:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in the most part
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.50,0:51:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,About 67%
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.18,0:51:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Big standard committee (National oil fuel and lubricant technology committee) has more
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.70,0:51:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Standard Committee has almost
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.98,0:51:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,over 90% as what I remember
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.86,0:51:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is people in this industry
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.58,0:51:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Standard Committee Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.90,0:51:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,is also in oil fuel industry
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.90,0:51:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this standard committee head
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.14,0:51:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is also in oil fuel industry
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.66,0:51:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought this before
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.66,0:51:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys have one-vote veto
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.94,0:51:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like it right?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.38,0:51:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmental Protect
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.38,0:51:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This wry smile from Yue Xing
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.06,0:51:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,gave me a strong memory
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.34,0:51:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He said I can only show my existance is
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.30,0:51:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when I stepped in to this door
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.38,0:51:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,write my name on the attendance sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.54,0:51:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because before I don’t even have ability to vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.86,0:51:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He said they want to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.58,0:51:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,push the quality of fuel become higher
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.98,0:51:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But the oil fuel industry normally explained like this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.02,0:51:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuel in our country has a majority part
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.62,0:51:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,come from middle east right?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.34,0:52:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Such as Iran’s fuel has a lot of sulfur
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.14,0:52:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In Tehran
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.34,0:52:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,they also surffering
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.58,0:52:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in this trouble come from bad quality fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.14,0:52:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Strong haze and fog
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.02,0:52:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But their problem is
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.18,0:52:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t have upgrade technology
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.70,0:52:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But chinese company is not lack of this type of technique
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.50,0:52:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the differences?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.10,0:52:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In Money
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.78,0:52:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,From National III to National IV
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.10,0:52:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,EPA said 7 cent per liter is enough
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.62,0:52:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Industry said no,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.62,0:52:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Need to be 50 cent
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.10,0:52:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I say both of you can sit down and show the cost
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.78,0:52:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and calculate it
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.58,0:52:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Calculate how much it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.26,0:52:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It is very simple
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.18,0:52:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He had another wry smile
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.66,0:52:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t say me,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.82,0:52:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you can go ask National Development and Reform Commission (NDRC) Economic Department
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.26,0:52:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,See if they can know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.62,0:52:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Cannot control
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.66,0:52:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Such as you have the only born child
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.10,0:52:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He want to learn something bad
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.42,0:52:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do as a mom
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.30,0:52:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Only thing you can do is beat him
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.98,0:52:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t beat him everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.74,0:52:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people have 10 child
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.90,0:52:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they are not naughty
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.38,0:52:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They are in front of you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.62,0:52:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t answer us
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.90,0:52:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The deputy unit
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.78,0:52:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.94,0:52:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They answer you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.78,0:52:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Price department don’t increase this year
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.42,0:52:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Next year come to your door
